Kwale Governor Salim Mvurya has congratulated the Health department for winning the Coast Malaria Award 2018, which means the county is the best in managing malaria spread. The ceremony was hosted by Population Services International Kenya. Addressing the media outside his Kwale office yesterday, Mvurya said the recognition is as a result of the good work done by county health practitioners. “I appreciate the efforts of all the health practitioners. I am proud of you for being part of the Health sector transformation,” the governor said. He urged county employees to emulate the Health department efforts to improve services. The best health facility award went to Msambweni County Referral Hospital, while the second best facility winner was Kikoneni Dispensary. Ng’ombeni Dispensary was third.